{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Inclusion of No Deal Brexit be a condition for any second referendum.",
        "additional_details": "Throughout the Brexit process the public have been informed that No Deal was better than a bad deal, despite a bad being being offered MPs have chosen to remove No Deal as an option without public consultation, limiting future options to either: the deal (widely accepted as bad) or remain.",
        "background": "We demand that to ensure a true democratic decision be taken by the public, it is a condition for any 2nd referendum on Brexit that the option of No Deal be included.",
